      <h1 class="page">Current course structure</h1>
      <p class="lede">This section will provide a high-level overview of the current MPM structure, including the sequence of units, credit point requirements, core units, elective options and pathway considerations.<br><br>Aim: To establish a shared understanding of how the degree is currently structured before identifying areas for improvement.</p>

      <div class="card award">
        <div class="award-h">Award requirements — 72 credit points</div>
        <p>To qualify for the award of the Master of Project Management, a candidate must complete <b>72 credit points</b>, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>24 cp of Project Management <b>Technical Core</b> units</li>
          <li>12 cp of Project Management <b>Leadership Core</b> units</li>
          <li>6 cp of Project Management <b>Strategic Core</b> units</li>
          <li>30 cp from either the research pathway or the coursework pathway.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="award-cols">
          <div>
            <div class="award-sub">Coursework pathway — 30 cp electives</div>
            <ul>
              <li>Min 6 / max 18 cp of <b>Technical</b> electives</li>
              <li>Min 6 / max 18 cp of <b>Strategic</b> electives</li>
              <li>Min 6 / max 18 cp of <b>Leadership</b> electives</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="award-sub">Research pathway — 18 cp thesis + 12 cp electives</div>
            <ul>
              <li>18 cp of <b>Thesis</b> units</li>
              <li>6 cp of <b>Strategic</b> elective units</li>
              <li>6 cp of <b>Leadership</b> elective units</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

